OSCAd (filename or packagename is oscad) be metonymic with
[Telekom] (O)pen (S)ource (C)compliance (Ad)visor. OSCAd 
is the interactive version of OSLiC, the open source 
license Compendium and shall interactively specify how to to
use open source Software compliantly. Particularly
it shall ...

(a) support open source users to act according to the open
source license requirements without having to become license
experts themselves

(b) offer strongly reliable and quickly accessible instructions 
(to-do lists) how to fulfill a touched open source license

The OSCAd is a Rweb based html frontend combined with a php
backend which delivers the fitting to-do lists.

(c) K. Reincke, Deutsche Telekom AG, Darmstadt 2013


